text: Ilex williamsii is a species of plant in the family Aquifoliaceae. It is endemic to Honduras. It is a seldom collected species of cloud forest and is of a terrestrial ecozone. The plant is critically endangered as of 1998. ==References== williamsii Category:Endemic flora of Honduras Category:Critically endangered flora of North America Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot Category:Plants described in 1951
